8 Complete and record the recommendation
For each CMP, save:

the original data files and their units;
the 2019–2023 average for each index;
every annual relative index (R_{j,y});
the combined annual indices (A_y);
the recent-year indicator (I);
the preliminary harvest-rule result (C^*);
the previous-advice value and annual-change adjustment;
the unrounded and rounded total recommendation;
any allocation calculation; and
all missing-data, revision, or exceptional-circumstances warnings.

The current simulations divide the total catch among fisheries using their average catch shares over the previous five years. The Scientific Committee should confirm whether that calculation is part of the CMP or a separate allocation decision.

2 Information that must accompany each CMP
Every CMP version must link to:

the method used to calculate its indicator, harvest control rule, and catch allocation;
all parameter values and annual data requirements;
the exact saved version of jmMSE used for evaluation;
OM and robustness scenario definitions;
definitions of the performance measures and links to the saved results;
review findings and known limitations; and
the decision that changed its status.

Purpose
This site describes the candidate management procedures (CMPs) being evaluated for South Pacific jack mackerel. It draws mainly on the current jmMSE analysis and brings together:

the MP29 and MP32 candidate definitions advanced into robustness testing;
six additional CMP comparison cases that isolate important choices;
the full management strategy evaluation (MSE) process;
evidence from tuning, trade-off, and robustness comparisons; and
instructions for applying a selected procedure when new annual data become available.

SCW17 Papers 03, 04, 08, and 09 provide historical context and documentation structure, but they do not define the current candidate registry.
The MSE calculations remain in SPRFMO/jmMSE. This site records what each CMP is, why it remains under consideration, how it would be applied, and which analysis supports it.

5 Annual application requirements still to resolve

authoritative provider and annual cutoff for each index;
precise index standardization performed by cpues.ind and the software version used;
treatment of missing or revised indices;
catch units and rounding;
approved catch-allocation update rule; and
exceptional-circumstances review and decision process.

3 Required calculation
Document, in order:

data checks and exclusions;
calculation of the stock or index indicator;
indicator and reference period used by the rule;
HCR equation and every parameter;
interannual constraints;
rounding and numerical precision;
allocation among fisheries or stocks; and
exceptional-circumstances checks.

